section.para:
To enable PostgreSQL, add the following to your configuration.nix:
= true; = pkgs.postgresql94;
Note that you are required to specify the desired version of PostgreSQL (e.g. pkgs.postgresql96Packages). Since upgrading your PostgreSQL version requires a database dump and reload (see below), NixOS cannot provide a default value for such as the most recent release of PostgreSQL.

For example, to enable the PostGIS and TimescaleDB extension, you can
say:


services.postgresql.plugins = p: with p;
  [ postgis
    timescaledb
  ];
